7.5: Introduced massive improvements for very large lookup tables (tens of thousands of rows).
It improved the compilation time and reduced the memory footprint for these tables.

7.6: Refined the execution speed of these large tables even further, specifically
optimizing how the Rete algorithm handles large-scale data updates against static lookup data.


